<inglise> Council Regulation (EEC) No 4045/89 of 21 December 1989 on scrutiny by Member States of transactions forming part of the system of financing by the Guarantee Section of the European Agricultural Guidance and Guarantee Fund and repealing Directive 77/435/EEC </inglise>
<eesti> N&Otilde;UKOGU M&Auml;&Auml;RUS (EM&Uuml;) nr 4045/89 Euroopa P&otilde;llumajanduse Arengu- ja Tagatisfondi tagatisrahastu rahastamiss&uuml;steemi kuuluvate toimingute kontrollimise kohta liikmesriikide poolt ning direktiivi 77/435/EM&Uuml; kehtetuks tunnistamise kohta 21. detsember 1989 </eesti>
<inglise> THE COUNCIL OF THE EUROPEAN COMMUNITIES, </inglise>
<eesti> EUROOPA &Uuml;HENDUSTE N&Otilde;UKOGU, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the Treaty establishing the European Economic Community, and in particular Article 43 thereof, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse Euroopa Majandus&uuml;henduse asutamislepingut, eriti selle artiklit 43, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the proposal from the Commission (1), </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse komisjoni ettepanekut, (1) </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the opinion of the European Parliament (2), </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse Euroopa Parlamendi arvamust (2) </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas, under Article 8 of Council Regulation (EEC) No 729/70 of 21 April 1970 on the financing of the common agricultural policy (3), as last amended by Regulation (EEC) No 2048/88 (4), the Member States take the measures necessary to satisfy themselves that transactions financed by the European Agricultural Guidance and Guarantee Fund (EAGGF) are actually carried out and are executed correctly, to prevent and deal with irregularities and to recover sums lost as a result of irregularities or negligence; </inglise>
<eesti> ning arvestades, et: &uuml;hise p&otilde;llumajanduspoliitika rahastamist k&auml;sitleva n&otilde;ukogu 21. aprilli 1970. aasta m&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 729/70 (3) (viimati muudetud m&auml;&auml;rusega (EM&Uuml;) nr 2048/88) (4) artikli 8 alusel peavad liikmesriigid v&otilde;tma vajalikke meetmeid veendumaks, et Euroopa P&otilde;llumajanduse Arendus- ja Tagatisfondist (EAGGF) rahastatavad toimingud toimuvad tegelikult ja n&otilde;uetekohaselt, selleks et t&otilde;kestada ja k&auml;sitleda eeskirjade eiramist ning sisse n&otilde;uda eeskirjade eiramise v&otilde;i hooletuse tagaj&auml;rjel kaotatud summad; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas scrutiny of the commercial documents of undertakings received or making payments can be a very effective means of surveillance of transactions forming part of the system of financing by the Guarantee Section of the EAGGF; whereas this scrutiny supplements other inspections already carried out by the Member States; whereas, furthermore, national provisions relating to scrutiny which are more extensive than those provided for in the Regulation are not affected by this Regulation; </inglise>
<eesti> makseid saavate ja neid sooritavate ettev&otilde;tjate &auml;ridokumentide kontrollimine v&otilde;ib olla eriti t&otilde;hus vahend Euroopa P&otilde;llumajanduse Arengu- ja Tagatisfondi tagatisrahastu rahastamiss&uuml;steemi kuuluvate toimingute kontrollimiseks; nimetatud kontroll t&auml;iendab muid liikmesriikide tehtavaid kontrolle; lisaks sellele ei m&otilde;juta k&auml;esolev m&auml;&auml;rus kontrollimisega seotud siseriiklikke s&auml;tteid, mille kohaldamisel kontroll on k&auml;esoleva m&auml;&auml;ruses etten&auml;htust ulatuslikum; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas Member States must be encouraged to reinforce the scrutiny of commercial documents of undertakings receiving or making payments which they have carried out in accordance with Directive 77/435/EEC (5); </inglise>
<eesti> liikmesriike tuleb julgustada tugevdama makseid saavate ja neid sooritavate ettev&otilde;tjate &auml;ridokumentide kontrollimist, mida nad on seni teinud direktiivi 77/435/EM&Uuml; (5) kohaselt; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the implementation by Member States of the rules arising from Directive 77/435/EEC has disclosed the need for certain provisions of that Directive to be amended on the basis of experience gained; whereas in view of the nature of the provisions concerned the amendments should be included in a Regulation; </inglise>
<eesti> direktiivi 77/435/EM&Uuml; eeskirjade rakendamise k&auml;igus liikmesriikides on ilmnenud vajadus muuta m&otilde;ningaid k&otilde;nealuse direktiivi s&auml;tteid omandatud kogemuste p&otilde;hjal; k&otilde;nealuste s&auml;tete laadi silmas pidades tuleks muutused teha m&auml;&auml;rusega; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the documents used as a basis for such scrutiny should be determined in such a way as to enable a full scrutiny to be carried out; </inglise>
<eesti> sellise kontrollimise aluseks olevad dokumendid tuleks kindlaks m&auml;&auml;rata nii, et oleks v&otilde;imalik teha t&auml;ielik kontroll; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the undertakings to be scrutinized must be selected on the basis of the nature of the transactions carried out on their responsibility and the breakdown of the undertakings receiving or making payments according to their financial importance in the system of financing by the Guarantee Section of the EAGGF; </inglise>
<eesti> kontrollitavad ettev&otilde;tjad tuleb valida nende vastutusel teostatud tehingute laadi p&otilde;hjal ning v&otilde;ttes arvesse makseid saavate v&otilde;i neid sooritavate ettev&otilde;tjate jaotumist vastavalt nende majanduslikule t&auml;htsusele EAGGF tagatisrahastu rahastamiss&uuml;steemis; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas, furthermore, it is necessary to provide for a minimum number of inspections of commercial documents; whereas this number must be determined by a method which precludes substantial differences between the Member States by virtue of differences in the structure of their expenditure under the Guarantee Section of the EAGGF; whereas this method may be established by referring to the number of undertakings of a certain importance in the system of financing by the Guarantee Section of the EAGGF; </inglise>
<eesti> lisaks sellele on vaja ette n&auml;ha &auml;ridokumentide minimaalne kontrollimiste arv; k&otilde;nealune arv tuleb kindlaks m&auml;&auml;rata meetodiga, mis v&auml;listaks liikmesriikide vahel oluliste erinevuste tekkimise nende EAGGF tagatisrahastuga seotud kulude struktuurierinevuste t&otilde;ttu; sellise meetodi kehtestamisel v&otilde;ib v&otilde;tta v&otilde;rdlusaluseks nende ettev&otilde;tjate hulga, kellel on teatav t&auml;htsus EAGGF tagatisosakonna rahastamiss&uuml;steemis; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the powers of the officials responsible for scrutiny and the obligations on undertakings to make commercial documents available to such officials for a specified period and to supply such information as may be requested by them should be defined; whereas it should also be stipulated that commercial documents may be seized in certain cases; </inglise>
<eesti> m&auml;&auml;ratleda tuleks kontrollimise eest vastutavate ametnike volitused ja ettev&otilde;tjate kohustus teha &auml;ridokumendid nimetatud ametnikele t&auml;psustatud ajavahemiku jooksul k&auml;ttesaadavaks ning edastada ametnikele nende n&otilde;utud teavet; tuleks ette n&auml;ha, et teatavatel juhtudel v&otilde;ib &auml;ridokumente &auml;ra v&otilde;tta; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas it is necessary to organize cooperation among the Member States on account of the international structure of agricultural trade and with a view to the completion of the internal market; whereas it is also necessary for a centralized documentation system concerning undertakings receiving or making payments established in third countries to be set up at Community level; </inglise>
<eesti> p&otilde;llumajanduskaubanduse rahvusvahelise struktuuri t&otilde;ttu ja siseturu v&auml;ljakujundamist silmas pidades on vaja korraldada liikmesriikidevahelist koost&ouml;&ouml;d; peale selle on vaja luua &uuml;henduse tasandil keskne dokumendis&uuml;steem kolmandates riikides asuvate makseid saavate v&otilde;i neid sooritavate ettev&otilde;tjate kohta; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas, while it is the responsibility of the Member States in the first instance to adopt their scrutiny programmes, it is necessary that these programmes be communicated to the Commission so that it can assume its supervisory and coordinating role and to ensure that the programmes are adopted on the basis of appropriate criteria; whereas scrutiny can thus be concentrated on sectors or undertakings where the risk of fraud is high; </inglise>
<eesti> kuigi kontrolliprogrammide vastuv&otilde;tmise eest liikmesriikides vastutavad eelk&otilde;ige liikmesriigid, tuleb k&otilde;nealused programmid edastada komisjonile, et komisjon saaks t&auml;ita oma j&auml;relevalve ja koosk&otilde;lastamisega seotud &uuml;lesandeid, ning tagada programmide vastuv&otilde;tmine asjakohaste kriteeriumide p&otilde;hjal; seega oleks v&otilde;imalik suunata kontrollimine sellistesse sektoritesse v&otilde;i ettev&otilde;tjatele, kelle puhul pettuseoht on suur; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the departments carrying out scrutiny pursuant to this Regulation must be organized independently of the departments carrying out scrutiny prior to payment; </inglise>
<eesti> k&auml;esoleva m&auml;&auml;ruse kohaselt kontrollivad asutused peaksid olema organisatoorselt s&otilde;ltumatud asutustest, kes teostavad kontrolli enne makse sooritamist; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas it is essential that each Member State have a special department responsible for monitoring the application of this Regulation and for coordinating the scrutiny carried out in accordance with this Regulation; whereas the officials belonging to that department may make inspections of undertakings in accordance with this Regulation; </inglise>
<eesti> on h&auml;davajalik, et igal liikmesriigil oleks &uuml;ks asutus, kes vastutaks k&auml;esoleva m&auml;&auml;ruse kohaldamise j&auml;lgimise ja k&auml;esoleva m&auml;&auml;ruse kohaselt teostatud kontrolli koordineerimise eest; nimetatud asutuses t&ouml;&ouml;tavad ametnikud v&otilde;ivad ettev&otilde;tjaid kontrollida vastavalt k&auml;esolevale m&auml;&auml;rusele; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas encouragement for reinforcing the departments responsible for the application of this Regulation should be provided in the form of a temporary, degressive Community contribution towards the expenditure incurred by Member States in engaging extra staff and towards the costs of training staff and equipping the departments; Whereas it is necessary for an estimate to be made of </inglise>
<eesti> k&auml;esoleva m&auml;&auml;ruse kohaldamise eest vastutavate asutuste tugevdamist tuleks soodustada &uuml;henduse ajutise ja kahaneva panusega liikmesriikide kuludesse, mis tulenevad lisapersonali palkamisest ja koolitamisest ning asutuste sisseseadmisest; </eesti>
<inglise> the amount of the Community financing required for implementing this measure; whereas such amount forms part of the financial forecast appearing in point II of the Interinstitutional Agreement on budgetary discipline and improvement of the budgetary procedure (6) of 29 June 1988; whereas the appropriations actually available will be determined under the budgetary procedure in compliance with that agreement; </inglise>
<eesti> on vaja prognoosida k&otilde;nealuse meetme rakendamiseks vajaliku &uuml;hendusepoolse rahastamise suurus; k&otilde;nealune summa sisaldub 29. juuni 1988. aasta eelarvedistsipliini ja eelarvemenetluse t&auml;iustamist k&auml;sitleva institutsioonidevahelise kokkuleppe (6) II punktis esitatud finantsprognoosis; tegelikult kasutada olevad assigneeringud m&auml;&auml;ratakse kindlaks vastavalt eelarvemenetlusele ja koosk&otilde;las k&otilde;nealuse kokkuleppega; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas information collected during the scrutiny of commercial documents must be protected by professional secrecy; </inglise>
<eesti> &auml;ridokumentide kontrollimise k&auml;igus kogutud teabe suhtes peab kehtima ametisaladuse kaitse p&otilde;him&otilde;te; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas arrangements should be made for an exchange of information at Community level so that the results of the application of this Regulation can be used to greater effect, </inglise>
<eesti> k&auml;esoleva m&auml;&auml;ruse kohaldamise tagaj&auml;rgede tulemuslikumaks kasutamiseks tuleks kehtestada teabevahetamise kord &uuml;henduse tasandil, </eesti>
<inglise> HAS ADOPTED THIS REGULATION: </inglise>
<eesti> ON VASTU V&Otilde;TNUD K&Auml;ESOLEVA M&Auml;&Auml;RUSE. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 1 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 1 </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> This Regulation relates to scrutiny of the commercial documents of those entities receiving or making payments relating directly or indirectly to the system of financing by the Guarantee Section of the EAGGF, hereinafter called 'undertakings', in order to ascertain whether transactions forming part of the system of financing by the Guarantee Section of the EAGGF have actually been carried out and have been executed correctly. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolev m&auml;&auml;rus k&auml;sitleb EAGGF tagatisrahastu rahastamiss&uuml;steemiga otse v&otilde;i kaudselt seotud makseid sooritavate v&otilde;i saavate &uuml;ksuste (edaspidi "ettev&otilde;tjad") &auml;ridokumentide kontrollimist selleks, et teha kindlaks, kas EAGGF tagatisrahastu rahastamiss&uuml;steemi kuuluvad tehingud toimuvad tegelikult ja n&otilde;uetekohaselt. </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> For the purposes of this Regulation 'commercial documents' means all books, registers, vouchers and supporting documents, accounts and correspondence relating to the undertaking's business activity, as well as commercial data, insofar as these documents relate directly or indirectly to the transactions referred to in paragraph 1. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esoleva m&auml;&auml;rus kohaldamisel on "&auml;ridokumendid" k&otilde;ik ettev&otilde;tja majandustegevusega seotud raamatupidamisregistrid, registrid, maksedokumendid, t&otilde;endavad dokumendid, raamatupidamisdokumendid ja kirjavahetus ning &auml;riandmestik niiv&otilde;rd, kuiv&otilde;rd need on otse v&otilde;i kaudselt seotud l&otilde;ikes 1 osutatud tehingutega. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 2 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 2 </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> Member States shall carry out systematic scrutiny of the commercial documents of undertakings taking account of the nature of the transactions to be scrutinized. </inglise>
<eesti> Liikmesriigid kontrollivad s&uuml;stemaatiliselt ettev&otilde;tjate &auml;ridokumente, v&otilde;ttes arvesse kontrollitavate tehingute laadi. </eesti>
<inglise> Member States shall ensure that the selection of undertakings for scrutiny gives the best possible assurance of the effectiveness of the measures for preventing and detecting irregularities under the system of financing by the Guarantee Section of the EAGGF. </inglise>
<eesti> Liikmesriigid tagavad, et kontrollitavate ettev&otilde;tjate valik tagaks EAGGF tagatisrahastu rahastamiss&uuml;steemis eeskirjade eiramise v&auml;ltimiseks ja avastamiseks v&otilde;etud meetmete t&otilde;hususe. </eesti>
<inglise> Inter alia the selection shall take account of the financial importance of the undertakings in that system and other risk factors. </inglise>
<eesti> Valikut tehes v&otilde;etakse arvesse ettev&otilde;tjate majanduslikku t&auml;htsust k&otilde;nealuses s&uuml;steemis ja muid riskitegureid. </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> The scrutiny referred to in paragraph 1 shall apply, for each period of scrutiny referred to in paragraph 4 to a number of undertakings which may not be less than half the undertakings whose receipts or payments, or the sum thereof, under the system of financing by the Guarantee Section of the EAGGF, amounted to more than ECU 60 000 for the calendar year preceding the beginning of the period of scrutiny in question. </inglise>
<eesti> L&otilde;ikes 1 osutatud kontrollimist kohaldatakse igal l&otilde;ikes 4 nimetatud kontrolliperioodil v&auml;hemalt poolte ettev&otilde;tjate suhtes, kellel EAGGF tagatisrahastu rahastamiss&uuml;steemiga seotud laekumiste v&otilde;i maksete v&otilde;i kahe eelneva summa oli k&otilde;nealuse kontrolliperioodi algusele eelnenud kalendriaasta jooksul suurem kui 60 000 ek&uuml;&uuml;d. </eesti>
<inglise> For the period of scrutiny beginning in 1990 the amount of ECU 60 000 quoted in the first subparagraph shall be replaced by ECU 100 000 and by ECU 90 000 for that beginning in 1991. </inglise>
<eesti> Esimeses l&otilde;igus nimetatud 60 000 ek&uuml;&uuml;d asendatakse 1990. aastal algava kontrolliperioodi puhul 100 000 ek&uuml;&uuml;ga ja 1991. aastal algava kontrolliperioodi puhul 90 000 ek&uuml;&uuml;ga. </eesti>
<inglise> It shall be compulsory for undertakings the sum of whose receipts or payments amounted to more than ECU 200 000 and which were not scrutinized in accordance with this Regulation during the preceding scrutiny period to be scrutinized. </inglise>
<eesti> Igal juhul tuleb kontrollida neid ettev&otilde;tjaid, kelle laekumiste v&otilde;i maksete summa oli suurem kui 200 000 ek&uuml;&uuml;d ja keda eelmise kontrolliperioodi jooksul k&auml;esoleva m&auml;&auml;ruse kohaselt ei kontrollitud. </eesti>
<inglise> Undertakings the sum of whose receipts or payments amounted to less than ECU 10 000 shall be scrutinized in accordance with this Regulation only for specific reasons to be indicated by the Member States in their annual programme as referred to in Article 10 or by the Commission in any proposed amendment to that programme. </inglise>
<eesti> Ettev&otilde;tjaid, kelle laekumiste v&otilde;i maksete summa oli v&auml;iksem kui 10 000 ek&uuml;&uuml;d, kontrollitakse k&auml;esoleva m&auml;&auml;ruse kohaselt ainult konkreetsete p&otilde;hjuste korral, millest liikmesriigid peavad teatama oma artiklis 10 nimetatud aastaprogrammis v&otilde;i millest teatab komisjon selle programmi muutmise taotluses. </eesti>
<inglise> 3. </inglise>
<eesti> 3. </eesti>
<inglise> In appropriate cases, the scrutiny provided for in paragraph 1 shall be extended to natural and legal persons with which undertakings within the meaning of Article 1 are associated and to such other natural or legal persons as may be relevant for the pursuit of the objectives set out in Article 3. </inglise>
<eesti> Vajalikel juhtudel laieneb l&otilde;ikes 1 s&auml;testatud kontrollimine f&uuml;&uuml;silistele ja juriidilistele isikutele, kes on seotud l&otilde;ikes 1 m&auml;&auml;ratletud ettev&otilde;tjatega, ning artiklis 3 s&auml;testatud eesm&auml;rkide saavutamisest l&auml;htuvalt ka teistele f&uuml;&uuml;silistele ja juriidilistele isikutele. </eesti>
<inglise> 4. </inglise>
<eesti> 4. </eesti>
<inglise> The scrutiny period shall run from 1 July to 30 June of the following year. </inglise>
<eesti> Kontrolliperiood kestab 1. juulist j&auml;rgmise aasta 30. juunini. </eesti>
<inglise> Scrutiny shall cover at least the calendar year preceding the scrutiny period; it may be extended for a period to be determined by the Member State which precedes that calendar year as well as the period between the 1 January of the year in which the period of control commenced and the effective date of control of an undertaking. </inglise>
<eesti> Kontrollimine h&otilde;lmab v&auml;hemalt kontrolliperioodile eelneva kalendriaasta; seda v&otilde;ib pikendada k&otilde;nealusele kalendriaastale eelneva ajavahemiku v&otilde;rra, mille m&auml;&auml;rab liikmesriik, v&otilde;i ajavahemiku v&otilde;rra, mis kestab kontrolliperioodi alguse aasta 1. jaanuarist kuup&auml;evani, mil algab ettev&otilde;tja tegelik kontrollimine. </eesti>
<inglise> 5. </inglise>
<eesti> 5. </eesti>
<inglise> The scrutiny carried out pursuant to this Regulation shall not prejudice the inspections undertaken pursuant to Article 6 of Regulation (EEC) No 283/72 (7) or those undertaken pursuant to Article 9 of Regulation (EEC) No 729/70. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esoleva m&auml;&auml;ruse kohane kontrollimine ei piira kontrollimist m&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 283/72 (7) artiklile 6 v&otilde;i m&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 729/70 artiklile 9. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 3 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 3 </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> The accuracy of primary data under scrutiny shall be verified in appropriate cases by an adequate number of cross-checks, including, inter alia: </inglise>
<eesti> Kontrollitavate p&otilde;hiandmete &otilde;igsuses veendumiseks tehakse asjakohastel juhtudel vajalik arv ristkontrollimisi, kuhu muu hulgas kuulub: </eesti>
<inglise> - comparisons with the commercial documents of suppliers, customers, carriers and other third parties directly or indirectly connected with transactions carried out within the financing system by the EAGGF Guarantee section, </inglise>
<eesti> - EAGGF tagatisrahastu rahastamiss&uuml;steemi raames teostatud tehingutega otse v&otilde;i kaudselt seotud tarnijate, klientide, veoettev&otilde;tjate ja muude kolmandate isikute &auml;ridokumentidega v&otilde;rdlemine, </eesti>
<inglise> - physical checks upon the quantity and nature of stocks, and </inglise>
<eesti> - varude hulga ja laadi f&uuml;&uuml;siline kontroll ja </eesti>
<inglise> - comparison with the records of financial flows leading to or consequent upon the transactions carried out within the financing system by the EAGGF Guarantee section. </inglise>
<eesti> - EAGGF tagatisrahastu rahastamiss&uuml;steemi raames teostatud tehingutele eelnevate v&otilde;i neist tulenevate finantsvoogude v&otilde;rdlemine raamatupidamisdokumentidega. </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> In particular, where undertakings are required to keep particular book records of stock in accordance with Community or national provisions, scrutiny of these records shall, in appropriate cases include a comparison with the commercial documents and, where appropriate, with the actual quantities in stock. </inglise>
<eesti> Eelk&otilde;ige siis, kui ettev&otilde;tjad peavad &uuml;henduse v&otilde;i siseriiklike &otilde;igusaktide kohaselt pidama varude kohta eraldi raamatupidamisregistrit, kuulub asjakohastel juhtudel kontrollimisse v&otilde;rdlus &auml;ridokumentidega ja vajaduse korral varu tegeliku suurusega. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 4 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 4 </eesti>
<inglise> Undertakings shall keep the commercial documents referred to in Articles 1 (2) and 3 for at least three years, starting from the end of the year in which they were drawn up. </inglise>
<eesti> Ettev&otilde;tjad s&auml;ilitavad artikli 1 l&otilde;ikes 2 ja artiklis 3 nimetatud &auml;ridokumente v&auml;hemalt kolm aastat alates selle aasta l&otilde;pust, mille jooksul need on koostatud. </eesti>
<inglise> The Member States may prescribe a longer period for the retention of these documents. </inglise>
<eesti> Liikmesriigid v&otilde;ivad dokumentide s&auml;ilitamiseks n&auml;ha ette pikema t&auml;htaja. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 5 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 5 </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> The persons responsible for the undertakings shall ensure that all commercial documents and additional information requested are supplied to the officials responsible for the scrutiny or to the persons empowered for that purpose. </inglise>
<eesti> Ettev&otilde;tjate eest vastutavad isikud tagavad, et k&otilde;ik n&otilde;utavad &auml;ridokumendid ja lisateave esitatakse kontrollimise eest vastutavatele ametiisikutele v&otilde;i selleks volitatud isikutele. </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
